class_description:
Dictionary has two subscripting interfaces:
Subscripting with a key, yielding an optional value:
Subscripting with an index, yielding a key-value pair:

Methods.method_description: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two values are not equal.
Methods.method_declar: static func != (lhs: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index, rhs: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> Bool

Methods.method_description: Returns a partial range extending upward from a lower bound.

params.param_description: The lower bound for the range.

Methods.method_declar: postfix static func ... (minimum: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> PartialRangeFrom<Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index>

Methods.method_description: Returns a partial range up to, and including, its upper bound.

params.param_description: The upper bound for the range.

Methods.method_declar: prefix static func ... (maximum: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> PartialRangeThrough<Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index>

Methods.method_description: Returns a closed range that contains both of its bounds.

params.param_description: The lower bound for the range.
The upper bound for the range.

Methods.method_declar: static func ... (minimum: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index, maximum: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> ClosedRange<Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index>

Methods.method_description: Returns a partial range up to, but not including, its upper bound.

params.param_description: The upper bound for the range.

Methods.method_declar: prefix static func ..< (maximum: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> PartialRangeUpTo<Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index>

Methods.method_description: Returns a half-open range that contains its lower bound but not its upper bound.

params.param_description: The lower bound for the range.
The upper bound for the range.

Methods.method_declar: static func ..< (minimum: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index, maximum: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> Range<Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index>
static func < (lhs: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index, rhs: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> Bool

Methods.method_description: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the value of the first argument is less than or equal to that of the second argument.
Methods.method_declar: static func <= (lhs: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index, rhs: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> Bool
static func == (lhs: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index, rhs: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> Bool

Methods.method_description: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the value of the first argument is greater than that of the second argument.
Methods.method_declar: static func > (lhs: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index, rhs: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> Bool

Methods.method_description: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the value of the first argument is greater than or equal to that of the second argument.
Methods.method_declar: static func >= (lhs: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index, rhs: Dictionary<Key, Value>.Index) -> Bool

return_description: true if lhs is greater than or equal to rhs; otherwise, false.
